  "text": "Western blots on total cell lysates (10 6 cells) were performed as described. [CITATION_1] Blots were incubated overnight at 4°C with primary antibodies: rabbit anti-TCF-1 (kindly provided by Y. Katsura, Kyoto, Japan), anti-active ␤-catenin (8E7; Upstate, Charlottesville, VA), anti-␤-catenin (clone [CITATION_2] , and anti-␥-catenin (clone 15; BD Transduction Laboratories, Lexington, KY) or anti-␣-tubulin (B-5-1-2; Sigma, St Louis, MO). Western blots were revealed with horseradish peroxidase (HRP)-conjugated anti-mouse and -rabbit Abs (Sigma) followed by enhanced chemiluminescence detection (Pierce, Rockford, IL).",
